description: From French inadmissible, from Middle French inadmissible.

adjectives.description: inadmissible (comparative more inadmissible, superlative most inadmissible)

entries.meaning: Not admissible, especially that cannot be admitted as evidence at a trial.
A person who is not to be admitted (to a country, a group, etc).
examples: June saw a decline in Southwest Border apprehensions and inadmissibles by 18 percent compared to May. This decline follows the overall downward trend for this time of year as apprehensions and inadmissibles along the Southwest Border have declined from May to June.
